        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 10 at 4:47PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 447 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 15
miles southwest of Abbeville, or near Lake Strom Thurmond, moving
east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Bobby Brown State Park, Lake Strom Thurmond, Calhoun Falls, Lake
Russell, Richard B Russell Dam, Bobby Brown State Recreation Area,
and Rice Town.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
